PGA CHAMPIONSHIP
August 17, 2006
John Aber
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








Q.  Talk about the experience playing in your second PGA Championship.
JOHN ABER:  It's a great experience.  It's great fun.  It's great to be here.  It's the best players in the world, and I'm honored to be here.
Q.  Talk about the course a little bit, how it's laid out.  There was talk about how the course had changed coming to the championship.  Talk about the course a little bit.
JOHN ABER:  The course is great.  I think it's very fair.  It's right in front of you, it's in perfect condition, and it's just a beautiful place.
Q.  Kind of compare your two experiences between this year and then 2001, some similarities, some differences, and your experiences with both of them.
JOHN ABER:  You know, very similar.  I enjoyed the Atlanta Athletic Club, also.  You know, it's hard to compare the two.  That was six years ago.  Both of them great fun, great experience.  You know, it's just a great honor to be here.
Q.  What are you looking at for tomorrow?
JOHN ABER:  Just go out and try to play as well as I can.  I'll have to try to shoot under par, and I'll go out and try my hardest.


